<p><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER" bgcolor="000000">
<tr>
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" align="CENTER">
<tr bgcolor="999999">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td width="10"><img src="http://www.maximumeq.com/forum/Images/SmallNew.gif" border="0" alt="New Message"></td><td width="50%"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>RE:How do we make money? (modified 0 times)</b> </font></td><td width="50%" align="RIGHT"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="EEEEEE"><b>murlow</b></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td><a href="UltraBoard.cgi?Action=ShowProfile&ID=murlow&Board=magician&Idle=30&Sort=0&Order=Descend&Page=0&Session=" target="Profile" OnMouseOver="window.status='View murlow (murlow) Profile.';return true;" OnMouseOut="window.status=''"><font face="Verdana" size="1" color="000000 ">Profile</font></a></td><td align="RIGHT"></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="EEEEEE">
<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I'm a 19 DE magician playing on Valon Zek (team PvP), so this really applies mostly to darkies but I think some will help you misguided lovers of the Light.  At low levels there wasn't a whole lot different that I could do to make money that was much different than any other newbie player (say levels 1 thru 8). You need to scrimp and save your cash for your level 4 spells by turning in firebeetle eyes and spiderling silks.  In addition to spell cost you'll need to buy malachites from your guild so save like a miser.  Once you get pets it's easier, as you can solo some and don't need to share loot with a party.  In Nektulos forest kill Large Spiders for their silk.  With a sewing kit you can combine the silks to make swatches which are stackable.  Swatches sell for like 2-3gold each.  Since I had a sewing kit I also made patchwork, from the wolf pelts that I would harvest. You can sell the pw to classes that can wear it or right back to the place that you buy the patterns from. Make bandages and sell 'em for about 1gold per 10.  Don't expect to get rich doing it, there doesn't seem to be a huge market for summoned bandages, but every once in awhile a higher level player will want to buy some and will treat you well.  Harvest bonechips from decaying skellies - necros and SK's will buy 'em for 1plat a stack of 20, sometimes more (sometimes ALOT more).  Once in awhile the skellies will have a nice weapon that you can sell or sharpen to tarnished condition (building your smithing skill) and sell to vendors.  Not much market for tarnished weapons but now and then someone will want to buy one.  <p>

Hang in there til you make 8, get a water pet spell.  I never bought any of the other elementals til i made 16.  Make a bunch of bandages for yourself.  Using the waterpet go to a place where there are asps, like the desert's edge in E. Commons.  Kill 'em by assisting your water pet during melee.  When you're poisoned keep bandaging - you'll outlast the poison 9 times out of 10.  Asps drop Giant Snake Fangs and poison sacks.  You can sell 'em to vendors for about 4gold each, sometimes other players want a good piercing weapon and you can sell the fang for more.  If you're in the area of Blackburrow, fight the snakes in there.  They drop the same fangs/poison sacks and you never get poisoned.  By this time you would probably have gotten your summon food/water spells, use 'em to feed yourself and don't spend cash on food.  You can also try Innothule swamp for the lower level froglocks that drop woven/mesh armor and you can wear it or sell it to other magic users and monks.  I'm 19 and all my armor is from the swamps or raw silk.  Be careful - the frogs will swarm but you can get by if you pick your fights carefully.  <p>

By level 12 you should be able to handle N.Ro tarantulas and asps with no problems - they drop more silk and fangs, or travel to the Feerot and fight the lizard men.  In the far northwest corner of the map there's a camp that only spawns 2 lizard men, you will be strong enough to take 'em both.  These guys drop weapons and sometimes 2-3 gold and it's a nice change of pace.  Watch out for patrolling Ogre guards if you're not well liked by the evils.<p>

At 16 buy all the backpacks you can carry, find yourself a partner and head to Sister Island in the Ocean of Tears (OoT).  If you're a darkie (like me) jump off the boat when you can see the island and swim for shore.  Kill the Sisters by pulling them down to the water's edge.  Almost EVERY Sister will drop a Purity belt plus small change.  These sell to vendors for 1.2plat each.  Ditch the rusty halberds they carry, it's just dead weight.  Stay 'til you fill all the empty backpacks and gate home, or take a canoe and intercept the boat (ram it in the side and you'll appear below deck). Gating is easier, you may want to bind close to the docks.  Experience is fair and I never made a trip there with out making 50-55pp.  You may want to try this at level 12 with a small party, but you have to share the loot.  Sisters also drop Words, which you need for researching spells.  Other research items (runes, pages, necro words) can be traded to other magic users or sold to vendors.  I made enough cash in OoT to buy and FBR and still have 30plat left over.  At lvl 17 or 18, I camped Ratraz with a partner in Neriak 3rd Gate.  Ratraz drops a club worth 5pp every kill.  You and your partner will need to give 5 bottles of red wine to Lotroz (think that's his name) the scribe in the left room of the Library to keep your faction even.  In fact, start out by giving him 20 bottles of red wine before your 1st kill of Ratraz.  It's easier to keep your faction up than it is to repair bad faction and if you drop to less than amiable Lotroz may not accept the wine.  You can buy the wine next door to where Ratraz spawns, it's like 7sil each - chicken feed to a person just back from OoT.<p>

That's about all the tips I have on making cash in EQ, except for these final two:  1)Sometimes a hi-level player will be  killing guards.  They're useually doing this for experience and not the weapons that the guard carries.  If you politely ask to loot the guard and you're given permission you can sell the guard's weapon/shield for several plat.  The guard killer often doesn't mind this as he doesn't want to be weighted down by the guard's stuff.  2) And finally - if you're playing on a crowded blue server consider switching to one of the less crowded servers or come to one of the Zeks.  Less people = more loot/experience.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
