<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">As a Mage you will be broke as hell in your early levels. I think the most money I ever had was alittle over 100pp up till lvl 24. Soon as I hit lvl 24 the money started rolling in. This is where your strenght as a Mage starts to show. Most other classes are worried so much about there wieght so they can't loot alot of weapons to sell. Monks have the hardest time with this.  But as a Mage you don't have to worry about being encumbered because you summon a bag that has 100% wieght reduction. And thats your key to getting rich. Try this idea when you hit lvl 24. Bind yourself at the Guard Tower on the Stone Bridge in North Karana then head to South Karana and get into an "Outside Paw Group". Summon like 2 to 3 of those bags and fill them with Fine Steal Weapons which sell for like 4-6pp a piece. Then when you are full gate back and sell. Don't keep items of importance in these bags because if you go LD you will lose them. <p>

Try this and see if it helps</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
