<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I am a Lvl 7 magician (1/2 bubble from 8) so I can only speak for earning money when you are a low level.<p>

Put some Training into a skill - Fishing, Bind wounds, and Tailoring (is the way I went, you might want to try another)<p>

Fishing - buy pole and bait and fish while you med ( you get xp for fishing and medding.)<br>
Bait cost me 3cp and fish bring me 1sp 5cp for a 1sp 2cp profit.  good for starters if you are going to be increasing your skill medding and cant move anyway. Also pulls up things like tattered sandels (AC 1), scales and tarnished dagger (wont go away when you log)<p>

Bind Wounds - buy spell create bandages and either either sell bandages or bind wounds (depending on your inclination, and believe me a fighter with less than 1 bubble of hp sitting in a zone away from a city with no cleric will be happy to pay for your bandaging).  Last night I applied bandages (will restore up to 50% hp) to a 19th Lvl Fighter that didnt even know he could do it himself.<p>

Tailoring - I put some Training into Tailoring and bought the Tailoring Book and a Large Sewing kit,(so I could make any kind of armor or backpack). I think you have to have the book with you, but not sure ... just had more success with the book...you dont have to hold it, I just keep mine in a backpack on me.<br>
 <br>
  SILK SWATCHS for RAW SILK ARMOR (direction below) become trivial to create at skill lvl 17 but never fail<br>
  PATCHWORK ARMOR - Trivial at skill lvl 26 (im told),Magic users cant wear patchwork (can sell or trade though)<br>
  RAW SILK ARMOR - Trivial at skill lvl 36, magic users and monks wear silk<br>
  BACKPACKS - (requires quality bear skin) 15% chance at Skill lvl 35, Trivial at skill lvl 88.<br>
 <br>
To create PATCHWORK ARMOR just combine 1 ruined pelt with 1 pattern in sewing kit. - I started with wolf pelts (SMALL Patchwork ARMOR for Dwarf,Elf,Halfling,Gnone) because they were easier to kill and I'm a High-Elf. When you get more exp at sewing, Ruined cat pelts( MEDIUM Patchwork ARMOR for Barbarian,Elf,Erudite,Half-Elf,Human) and Ruined Bear (LARGE Patchwork ARMOR for Barbarian,Ogre,Troll).<p>

To create SILK SWATCH for RAW SILK ARMOR<br>
 Combine 2 spider (not spiderling) silks in kit to make a silk swatch.<br>
 1 Silk Swatch combined with pattern (also about 5sp) to make silk armor. <p>

To create BACKPACKS - Combine Quality Bear Skin with pattern, Same as regular but have 10 slots</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
